Which option to ssh specifies the private key to use for authentication?
A)  - m
B)  - i
C)  - k
D)  - a
B
B. The - i option is used to specify a private key to use for authentication with SSH. Ofthe other options, - a is used to disable forwarding of the authentication agent, - k disablesGSSAPI credentials, and - m specifies message authentication code (MAC) algorithms.
